    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Centos Notes]]></title>
    <link href="http://dankuanmei.xyz/blog/2016/07/14/centos-notes/"/>
    <updated>2016-07-14T15:42:25+00:00</updated>
    <id>http://dankuanmei.xyz/blog/2016/07/14/centos-notes</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3>Adding, Enabling, and Disabling a Yum Repository</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>yum-config-manager --add-repo repository_url
</span><span class='line'>yum-config-manager --enable repository…
</span><span class='line'>yum-config-manager --disable repository…</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>List repo for centos:
* <a href="http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/">http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/6/x86_64/</a>
* <a href="http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/">http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/</a></p>

<h3>Fix error no key</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>wget http://ftp.riken.jp/Linux/fedora/epel/RPM-GPG-KEY-EPEL-6
</span><span class='line'>rpm -import RPM-GPG-KEY-EPEL-6
</span><span class='line'>rm -f RPM-GPG-KEY-EPEL-6
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>rpm --import http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/RPM-GPG-KEY-EPEL-6</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>You need to install and configure ntp.</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ yum install ntp
</span><span class='line'>$ chkconfig ntpd on
</span><span class='line'>$ ntpdate pool.ntp.org
</span><span class='line'>$ service ntpd start</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Useful &ldquo;df&rdquo; Commands to Check Disk Space in Linux</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
<span class='line-number'>13</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ df -a
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>Filesystem           1K-blocks      Used Available Use% Mounted on
</span><span class='line'>/dev/cciss/c0d0p2     78361192  23186116  51130312  32% /
</span><span class='line'>proc                         0         0         0   -  /proc
</span><span class='line'>sysfs                        0         0         0   -  /sys
</span><span class='line'>devpts                       0         0         0   -  /dev/pts
</span><span class='line'>/dev/cciss/c0d0p5     24797380  22273432   1243972  95% /home
</span><span class='line'>/dev/cciss/c0d0p3     29753588  25503792   2713984  91% /data
</span><span class='line'>/dev/cciss/c0d0p1       295561     21531    258770   8% /boot
</span><span class='line'>tmpfs                   257476         0    257476   0% /dev/shm
</span><span class='line'>none                         0         0         0   -  /proc/sys/fs/binfmt_misc
</span><span class='line'>sunrpc                       0         0         0   -  /var/lib/nfs/rpc_pipefs</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Download using wget or curl</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ wget -O ...
</span><span class='line'>$ curl -O ...</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Copy file to clipboard</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ xclip -sel clip &lt; ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Make simple server with python</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ python -m SimpleHTTPServer 8080</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Install nodejs</h3>

<p>Run as root on RHEL, CentOS or Fedora, for Node.js v4 LTS Argon:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ curl --silent --location https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_4.x | bash -</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Alternatively for Node.js v6:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ curl --silent --location https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_6.x | bash -</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Alternatively for Node.js 0.10:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ curl --silent --location https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup | bash -</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Then install, as root:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ yum -y install nodejs</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Install development tools</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ sudo yum groupinstall "Development Tools"</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Zip</h3>

<p>Zip folder to file</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ zip -r file_name.zip /path/of/folder/</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Auto start service</h3>

<p>Add it to chkconfig</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ sudo /sbin/chkconfig --add mysqld</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Make sure it is in the chkconfig.</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ sudo /sbin/chkconfig --list mysqld</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Set it to autostart</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ sudo /sbin/chkconfig mysqld on</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>To stop a service from auto starting on boot</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ sudo /sbin/chkconfig mysqld off</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Find text in folder</h3>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>$ grep -rnw './' -e ""   </span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

]]></content>
